Source: pg-command-fw
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), cargo, clang
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/rustwizard/pg_command_fw

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-command-fw
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-command-fw
Depends: postgresql-PGVERSION, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: DDL and utility command firewall for PostgreSQL
  pg_command_fw intercepts and selectively blocks DDL, utility commands,
  and dangerous built-in functions through configurable PostgreSQL hooks.
  This package builds the pgrx extension for PostgreSQL 15 through 18.
